Description:
Modern Beauty In Historic Surrounds
As the street name suggests, this polished single bedroom, two bathroom apartment takes its place within the historic Pentridge precinct, superbly placed just moments to beautiful Coburg Lake Reserve, eclectic Sydney Road shops and cafes, Upfield Bike Path, Merri Creek Trail and Coburg Train Station. Securely and swiftly accessed via elevator transit, savvy new buyers, astute investors and discerning downsizers will be pleasantly surprised by its spacious interior and clever design elements. The living area is open in configuration, well illuminated and boasts excellent entertaining credentials including a contemporary kitchen with stone counters and a full complement of appliances. A seamless transition to the adjoining, north facing alfresco terrace blurs the line between indoor and outdoor living. Covered for continuous use, it's completed with integrated cupboards and a relaxing day bed concealing storage and tempting hours of sundrenched relaxation. Uniquely indulgent, two full bathrooms include a chic ensuite with oversized shower and central combining laundry function. The bedroom is generously proportioned and incorporates mirrored built-in wardrobes and a dedicated study nook. Presenting perfectly in pristine condition and enhanced with additional sought after features of secure undercover parking, ample storage including cage plus split system air conditioning, inspection will leave you breathless.
Alexkarbon Real Estate Pty Ltd
122 Errol Street, North Melbourne VIC 3051

Description:
Live, Swim and Subdivide (STCA)!
This spacious character home is privately located on a sealed road with all services connected just a short stroll from the Cockatoo township & offers all the comforts & conveniences you could desire including an inground, solar heated, saltwater pool & enough room for the sheep, goat, pig or pony!
The home features wide hallways, high ceilings, ornate features, and year-round comfort is guaranteed with the gas ducted heating, evaporative cooling and the split system in the Family Room.
Situated on a fully fenced acre, perfect for the kids, fur babies & your hobby farm inhabitants, this weatherboard home features 3 spacious, robed bedrooms, the Master with walk in robe & ensuite.
There are 2 living areas including a formal lounge or lounge/dining area that could also be reworked as a Theatre Room and an open plan kitchen/family. The well-appointed, timber kitchen features a handy breakfast bar and room for any size fridge and all of this opens onto the enormous deck, perfect for entertaining the masses which overlooks the welcoming solar heated pool and your own, private acre of land.
Outside there is established gardens, a Man Cave, workshop, plenty of dry storage under the house and room to drive through to the back yard if you wanted to build a shed (STCA) or subdivide (STCA), plant an orchard or adopt a sheep or two down the track the options are endless.
Perfectly located and equipped for the whole family!
CALL SAMANTHA TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY! 0438 680 032

Description:
Private & Peaceful with a Big Shed
****Due to COVID-19 pandemic and current Metro stage 4 restrictions none of our properties are able to be attended for physical inspections. Please contact the listing agent for alternative virtual inspections and other viewing options.**** Thank you for your understanding!
If you are looking for a quiet, tranquil home to come back to after a busy day, this home may just be the one for you. This 2-storey home is nestled amongst almost 2/3 of an acre (2467m2) of low maintenance gardens and lush lawns, giving you complete privacy and serenity. The flexible floorplan of this home allows you to have the option of a 4th bedroom or 2nd living space accommodating for larger families.
Upstairs features the generously sized master bedroom with full ensuite. The remaining bedrooms on the top level on the home both have built-in robes and are serviced by the family bathroom. The kitchen has recently been renovated, with a spacious walk-in pantry, and top-quality appliances. There is also a family bathroom on this level. The comfortable living area of the home features an ambient wood heater, ducted heating and 2 split systems for all year comfort.
Downstairs features a multi-purpose room with a newly renovated bathroom, giving you the option to create an additional bedroom or rumpus room/ teenagers retreat.
Outside you are surrounded by fully fenced low maintenance gardens, and plush lawns with plenty of space for the kids or pets to play. The rear of the home features an outdoor dining area perfect for those warm summer nights enjoying a BBQ. While the front of the home features an expansive deck to enjoy the views of your gardens and feed the local birds. For the tradies or those that have a lot of stuff, youll be impressed with the parking and car accommodation, with a powered 2 car garage and ample off-street parking.
Private and peaceful this home is also spacious and flexible, located only a short distance to the local townships of Emerald and Cockatoo with their shops, schools, cafes and public transport makes this property a must-see. Contact Mick Dolphin 0429 684 522 or Janet Hawkins on 0409 117 432 to arrange an inspection.

Description:
Home amongst the Gum Trees
PLEASE CALL TO BOOK A PRIVATE INSPECTION TIME
Set on a quarter of an acre (approx.) in the leafy little town of Cockatoo, this classic 3 bedroom split level home is the perfect new home for you and your family.
The home features a study, 3 bedrooms all with built in robes, a study, main bathroom that opens to the master bedroom. The spacious lounge with Conara wood fire heating. Central kitchen area with lots of bench & pantry space, gas cooking & dishwasher. A second living room and a pool room or third living area down stairs great for teenage kids or guest accommodation. The second living area opens out to the deck area at the back of the home overlooking the private back yard, perfectly sprinkled with flowers, ferns, leafy green trees and shrubs backing onto crown land giving you the outlook of a large acreage property without the maintenance! Double carport, workshop and garden sheds for the green thumb or handy man
Packed with potential, the home offers an incredible blank canvas to add your own personal touches or just move in and leave as is. The perfect place to sit back and enjoy the tranquil sounds of the surrounding birdlife and soak in the beautiful bush setting
It is a short drive to the heart of town offering the new supermarket, a number of cafés, shops, buses and the iconic puffing billy railway line as well as a walking distance to the highly regarded primary school, kinder and child care centre. This home is ideal for anyone looking to move in to a beautiful country town surrounded by other families that have lived in the area for ever.

Description:
Hills home for the whole tribe
A charming country attitude exudes from the existing weatherboard home. Hang your boots on the porch under the leadlight windows and enter a main living area flooded with natural light. The gleaming bamboo floorboards shine through the dining, kitchen and family living area. Natural wood is showcased in the comfortable kitchen and enchanting tiles that range through the evocative colours of the fern gully outside the windows. The living area is curled around a wood-fired stove and there is ducted heating and multi-head split system to ensure year round comfort. Entertaining is simple with a sliding door out to the verandah overlooking an exceptional rainforest block that drops away to the creek alive with native wildlife.
A plenty of bedrooms; six are on offer in this large family home: four downstairs and two upstairs sharing a private balcony and split system. The bathroom looks out to the unfurling fronds and has slate flooring as does the separate laundry and toilet. The connecting staircase is crowned by wraparound windows which invite beautiful shafts of light into the centre of the home, and into the slate-floored second living area with a further wood-fired stove. Here, again sliding doors lead you out to the tiled terrace around the house which has enough room for a trampoline and is lined with fruit trees; apple, lemon and nectarine. There is also a woodshed and a tool shed bordering the flat parking area. The potential piggy bank here is limited only by your imagination. You could easily rent out and/or improve the existing house with an ensuite and some perceptive touches here and there.
2nd title also available by negotiation with Council-approved plans and permits for a 4 bedroom, 2 bath, 2 storey dwelling on the 1556m2 title. Call Katie Woods to request plans and discuss on 0428744498

Description:
Ignite Your Senses!
***AVAILABLE FOR VIEWING BY PRIVATE INSPECTION. CONTACT AARON DAY 0407 365 994 OR TYSON BLUHM 0437 843 820**
Thoughts of the Dandenong Ranges induce a flood of sensory information. You visualise giant green tree ferns and low clouds rolling over blue hills. You hear the laughter of the Kookaburras and the whistle of the iconic Puffing Billy as it trundles along the track. You smell the eucalyptus and crisp fresh air. You can almost taste the food from some of the regions award winning restaurants. And you think about mid-week breaks and weekend getaways.
This is your exclusive invitation to make these sensations part of your everyday life, with enough room for the extended family.
This dual accommodation estate is situated on 1 acre of meticulously maintained gardens and lawns between Cockatoo and Gembrook, along the Puffing Billy Railway line and with easy access to the Emerald - Gembrook Walking Trail.
The cottage has its own carport which has been thoughtfully divided from the main home by screening to ensure privacy. Just a few steps along a sealed path peppered by ornamental trees and shrubs, you reach the picturesque storybook cottage with covered veranda and gorgeous dormer windows. The interior of the cottage features a large lounge and dining area with cathedral ceilings, exposed beams and a gas log fire to cosy up next to, with all the ambiance of a wood fire without the hassle. The bright, functional kitchen features dishwasher, gas cooking and electric oven, and looks out over a private garden sitting area. There is an additional undercover entertaining area where you can enjoy a meal and wine outdoors when the weather is mild. The master suite features an ensuite with large sunken spa, the ultimate in relaxation in those cooler months. Upstairs are the two loft bedrooms, big enough to fit a double and a single bed, meaning the entire family can enjoy their own space. The cottage also features ducted heating and air conditioning for year round comfort.
The main home is a quality built solid brick home with a double carport at the entrance for convenience. The entry door is an oversized wood feature which produces an exciting impression of what lies behind it. Beautiful exposed brick walls and high cathedral ceilings with exposed beams and skylights provide a striking and light filled environment, consistent throughout the home. Immediately past the foyer is the large master suite with sitting room and ensuite with large spa, and a personal entrance through double sliding doors by a private courtyard. The windows here provide a unique aspect over the Puffing Billy Railway line.
Further into the home, off the wide hallway are 3 robed bedrooms serviced by a spacious bathroom. The hallway opens into the main living zone with dining area and commodious lounge with wood heater and windows that look out over the gardens and doors that provide access to the stunning inground pool, nestled aesthetically between the ferns.
Beyond, the main living zone features a well-appointed kitchen with double oven, cooktop and warming drawers and an informal dining area for serving up a quick bite. The laundry is also located here, in addition to the office or 5th bedroom.
Outside, there are undercover verandas on both sides of the home joined by a path that meanders easily through the gardens, designed to make the most of the natural surroundings and wildlife, while providing picturesque seating areas and maintaining privacy.
There is additional shedding with concrete floor and power and 2 garden sheds to house all the tools.
This property is currently known as The Whistle Stopover Bed and Breakfast, successfully trading in the region for many years due to its reputation for outstanding hospitality, pristine accommodations, and tranquil setting. It therefore provides a luxurious opportunity for 2 families to reside and contribute financially, or continue the Bed & Breakfast legacy.
This estate is nestled along the Puffing Billy Railway Line between the Gembrook and Cockatoo townships and is close to shops, public transport and the popular Emerald-Gembrook Walking Trail. It provides many possibilities for the discerning buyer so a viewing is essential.
CALL TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY!
Aaron Day 0407 365 994 or Tyson Bluhm 0437 843 820

Description:
THE ULTIMATE LIFESTYLE ON OVER HALF AN ACRE WITH VIEWS
Your dream of a spacious family home, tranquillity and a superb outdoor lifestyle is here with magnificent views of the cockatoo township, seen from almost every angle of the home, and really maximised with the big gazebo and decking to enjoy your morning coffee in peace.
As you walk through the front door the home is saturated with natural light from the large windows and open living space, kept warm in the winter by the flickering flame of the coonara. A quality kitchen with stainless steel appliances, flows seamlessly into the large adjoining dining room. There is a separate wing for two of the three bedrooms, all complete with built in robes. Featuring exposed beams, gas ducted heating and a fresh modern colour scheme throughout, this abode has all the creature comforts to make you feel right at home.
Outside offers an enormous useable backyard with established trees, another fantastic decked entertaining area that enjoys private picturesque views and is a great place to entertain your family and friends. Under house storage, plenty of parking, double carport, sealed drive, good sized garden shed and beautifully maintained established gardens including the orchard of lemons, grapefruits, mandarins, loquats, apples and figs that will fill your fruit basket all year round. Make the hills lifestyle yours today!

Description:
Simply Stunning Seclusion
Chiselled onto this 3068m2 plot, with Cockatoo Creek meandering through the southern corner, is a double-storey family home built with limestone blocks that contain the luxurious living within. Homes of this calibre are few and far between. The thoughtfulness of layout, build quality and elegance of interior design are 5 Star and all within easy walking distance of local sporting grounds, school bus and public bus routes.
The gated entrance that brings you up to the house on a newly sealed driveway to the triple garage with dual access for boat or trailer. Internal access from the garage into a hobby room, gym or study and then into the tiled lobby with beautiful double front doors, impressive extra-wide staircase and powder room. From here you have a choice of living area - the formal lounge with gas log fireplace, the family living with meals adjacent to the kitchen or head upstairs to the den/rumpus or open-plan office. Fully tinted picture windows (partly double-glazed) look onto the outdoor living, landscaped bush garden or into the solar-heated in-ground lap swimming pool which can be accessed from the hobby-room, the kitchen, the formal dining, the laundry and downstairs shower room.
The upsized opulence of the master suite will leave you breathless. The bedroom is itself approx 5m x 5m plus a fully fitted walk-in robe (with access to even more attic storage) and the fully tiled ensuite complete with dual vanity, large shower and corner spa looking out to the tree-tops. The second bedroom is almost as impressive; semi-ensuite, mirrored built-in wardrobes and access to a balcony shared with the upstairs living zone. The main bathroom is also fully tiled with a corner bath/step-in shower. Two further great sized bedrooms along the corridor both with BIR.
The bespoke kitchen with Caesarstone benchtops and inbuilt wine storage, benchtop cooking looking out into the family meals space and heaps of storage that continues into the laundry that matches the kitchen cabinetry styling.
This is a very comfortable home to snuggle-up in winter or splash-out during the summer months. Supersoft carpet underfoot, evaporative cooling, ducted heating, gas log fire, block-out and shade blinds. And whether you are rugged up or swimming tog clad, there are so many places to have fun and entertain. The poolside outdoor alfresco, the deck and built-in seating around the firepit, undercover dining AND the most amazing cubby house adventure play area.
The landscaping is a beautiful balance between formality and native bush garden. There is a veggie patch ready for the green of thumb and numerous fruits including a kiwi vine, apple, pear, nectarine, plum, kaffir lime, lime and lemon trees.
Please call Sue Colic on 0421 772 610 to book your private inspection time.

Description:
BIG, BEAUTIFUL AND BURSTING WITH FEATURES ON 2822Mm2
Custom built and renovated, this stunning, brick home is surrounded by colourful landscaped gardens that provide beauty from every angle. The home is nestled perfectly into its almost ¾ acre setting which is full fenced and offers all of the privacy you desire. Generous proportions and raked ceilings provided a sense of space throughout the huge living area and on to the open plan family, meals and kitchen. Stone benches, glass splashback, an abundance of cupboards, 900mm Ilve gas hot plates and oven and dishwasher caters to the largest of gatherings and allows the chef the very best environment to allow their creativity to flow. The family area is warmed by a gas log fire whilst the separate living room has an atmospheric wood fire as a centrepiece. Large windows allows a view of the entire property and enhances the beauty and café doors lead out to the covered entertainment area. There are four bedrooms, the master with full ensuite and walk in robe. Both bathrooms has been upgraded and feature walk in showers for ease of access and a luxurious spa bath to the family bathroom. Outdoors you will find, extensive paving, water feature, mature plantings, two double carports plus a mancave/storage shed and two sealed driveways. For those looking for a self-sufficient lifestyle there is a veggie patch area and an outbuilding that can be converted to a chicken pen as well. All services are connected and situated within easy reach of Cockatoo and Emerald townships and approx. 15 minutes to Pakenham plus buses at the top of the road to schools, the living is easy here. If space, privacy and a country lifestyle is what you are after, you need to arrange your private inspection today.

Description:
Excellent Opportunity!
***AVAILABLE FOR VIEWING BY PRIVATE INSPECTION. CONTACT AARON DAY 0407 365 994 OR TYSON BLUHM 0437 843 820***
Situated on a generous ½ acre block in a convenient Cockatoo location, this property presents an exciting opportunity for the discerning buyer.
With dual access of both Viewhill Road and Vincent Street, the property provides convenience and plenty of off street parking at the entrance of the dwelling.
Entrance is via a well lit, undercover alcove, directly into the open plan home with beam roof and exposed brick walls.
The expansive kitchen features timber cabinetry, slate flooring and abundant bench space for meal preparation and servery, all the while conversing easily with family and friends relaxing in the connecting dining space.
Views over the property are afforded by the windows in the generous sunken lounge with wall to wall carpet, open fire place and practical wood cavity so you can enjoy the views and relax in warmth and comfort.
The master bedroom is situated adjacent to the lounge, separated by the exposed brick wall so the noise transfer is minimal. Likewise it is sunken and robed, and captures views similar to the lounge.
There is an additional 2 bedrooms, one of which is robed, located close to the spacious main bathroom with slate flooring, separate toilet and corner spa bath.
There is an additional robed study which could easily become a fourth bedroom for the larger family, or office for those working from home.
Zoned Residential 1 on a large block with dual access, the property provides an opportunity to live comfortably now with the possibility of subdividing in the future (STCA), allowing financial freedom.
Properties of this type are becoming increasingly popular so don't miss your chance to inspect.
CALL TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY!
Aaron Day 0407 365 994 or Tyson Bluhm 0437 843 820

Description:
OPPORTUNITY & COMFORT WITH DUAL LIVING
Fantastic property in the middle of Cockatoo with oodles of everything for now and a nest egg for your future. A sub-dividable (STCA) flat open and sunny 1430m2 (the biggest block in the street) - just seconds from the primary school and minutes to the fancy new shopping centre. Do not underestimate the punch this property packs to the savvy investor or homemaker with a game plan.
The smart weatherboard house is spick and span with 3 carpeted bedrooms all with BIR and ceiling fans. A bright welcoming living area with split system and polished boards is sure to please, as is the cheerful kitchen/dining room with sliding doors to the back verandah. If peace of mind and creature comforts are high on your list of priorities this home will entice.
The spotless rentable 2-bedroom cottage at the rear of the block adds further flexibility to this super property. Complete with its own verandah, kitchen, bathroom and laundry, split system, ceiling fan and security system - this space is ideal for extended family, an elaborate home office or income earner.
This secure property is fully fenced and gated, front and back with a sealed driveway, a garage, a carport and gravelled area to the rear for further cars or largish toys to be safely stowed away. There is also a storage shed, a garden shed and two water tanks ensuring a supply for the soft green grass, camellias and lemons.
The unexpected surprise of a garden spa room with built-in TV just adds to the long list of features and comfort.
Cockatoo's market performance as a suburb just keeps going from strength to strength. And with a developing shopping precinct we predict the best is still to come.
Come to the open or book to inspect to understand how you could capitalise on this adaptable property.

Description:
Character, Charm and Convenience!
***AVAILABLE BY PRIVATE INSPECTION. CONTACT AARON DAY 0407 365 994 OR TYSON BLUHM 0437 843 820***
Are you looking for a family home with character, views and country charm? Then this is the place for you!
Set on ½ acre close to shops, schools and the local vet, this property is the ideal place to make family memories.
The elevated block and multi storey home provides pleasant views over the valley below and allows for an abundance of natural light to filter through the upper living area.
Entering the interior of the home you are struck by the expansive space, polished timber floors, white dado panelling and grand balustrade staircase. Beyond is the large, functional kitchen with white cupboards, timber bench tops, large island bench and an open fire place, creating the perfect atmosphere for wholesome country cooking.
The sun drenched dedicated dining area is the perfect place to relax and linger over a hearty lunch with the family, or eat outside on the undercover entertaining area easily accessed through classy French doors.
Also located on this level with irreplaceable double doors acquired from the historic Old Melbourne Wool Exchange, is a huge bedroom suite with open fire place and ornate lead light features and access onto the balcony where you can take in the views over your morning coffee.
The laundry and main bathroom is also located on this level for convenience.
Down the timber staircase is a good storage alcove or wine cellar and large living area with exposed brick walls and open fireplace and access outside.
Two bedrooms, one with ensuite sit off the living space where the gas console heater ensures warmth throughout.
Outside is the distinctive detached studio. Here are two additional rooms suiting teenagers, parents, artists, or those working from home.
Additional features of home include split system air conditioning, chook pen, wood shed and 4.5kW solar system to reduce your carbon footprint.
This property delivers in its distinguishing grand features, old world charm and delightful family environment.
CALL TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY!
Aaron Day 0407 365 994 or Tyson Bluhm 0437 843 820

Description:
TO VIEW THIS PROPERTY, PLEASE CALL THE AGENT TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION.
RIGHT HERE WAITING FOR YOU ON 980m2
Centrally located on a completely useable block of almost ¼ acre is this cedar weatherboard home that offers the perfect opportunity for you to secure your first home and enjoy the country lifestyle you have been looking for and still have everything at your fingertips. The home comprises 3 bedrooms all with built in robes, family bathroom complete with a bath, updated kitchen featuring stainless steel appliances including gas stove and dishwasher and a living room with the warmth and charm of polished floor boards, timber ceilings and exposed beams. Ducted gas heating, cosy wood fire and split system ensure year round comfort. Outdoors you can sit on the wrap around deck and relax, romp around in the fully fenced rear yard or potter amongst the established garden. There is a double garage with an area that is suitable as a workshop, studio, man cave or teenagers pad and under house storage. All of this is within walking distance of the shops, highly regarded Primary School and bus stop. If you love to be active you can stroll along the walking trails that will take you to Gembrook or, in another direction, to Emerald Lake Park and the Wright State Forest. Be sure to put this great property at the top of your list.

Description:
Give Me a Home Among The Gum Trees!
This charming property is located on almost ¾ acre with stunning views over the gum trees where you will feel a million miles away.
Entrance to the property is by a long driveway that curls around and provides off-street parking for the trailer, the boat, the caravan and the family vehicles.
The brick veneer home features 3 bedrooms, the master with private access to the main bathroom which contains a bath and separate shower, making this an ideal family home.
The lounge room is open and bright with floating floors, an open fire place and large windows that immediately capture your attention, making you feel cosy and warm on those foggy winter days. For the sunny summer months, the additional split system and forest views transport you to a cooler climate.
The kitchen also has windows overlooking the land, and the adjoining meals area has double glass sliding doors onto the rear deck where you can entertain friends and family in your own private rainforest.
The land at the rear has been terraced for maximum functionality and enjoyment and cascades into Cockatoo Creek below, a natural haven for wildlife.
This is your chance to secure a home that provides countless opportunities for the tranquil lifestyle of your dreams, in a quiet location only minutes from shops and schools.

Description:
COMFORT AND COMMUNITY
PRIVATE INSPECTIONS AVAILABLE ADHERING TO HYGIENE & SOCIAL DISTANCING GUIDELINES
This family home sits in the beating heart of the caring community of Cockatoo. From here, the children can walk to the local primary school or you can wander to town and stock up at the shiny new IGA. The fantastic Alma Treloar reserve is a stroll away and is packed with activities for all ages including a playground, murmuring creek and a soon to be opened BMX track.
Heading up the sealed driveway you find this welcoming 3 bedroom home nestled under mature lush green tree ferns. With new flooring, sophisticated palette throughout and contemporary lighting, the open plan living area gives a great reception. The bathroom has been transformed with care to create a gorgeous bright space for bathing and rejuvenation.
The kitchen/dining area shines with the morning sun illuminating the crisp white surfaces. Here is a home where you will really enjoy cooking for the family as you look across the dining area to the treetops brimming with Cockatoos and Rosellas. Step outside into the beautiful private garden room where you can enjoy your coffee listening to Puffing Billy tootling along at the bottom of the hill as you plan your walks on the many local bush tracks.
Sitting on a ¼ acre the back garden is open to the sun and has been terraced for easy gardening. It features a shed and side patio and has chickens scampering happily at the top of the block in their spacious run. Feast on the Fig, Kiwi and Plum trees whilst you decide what to plant next.
Come and enjoy the fresh country air at the open day.

Description:
Family Focused Design Inside and Out
With modern updates and a family focused design, this home suits house-proud buyers seeking something special. Situated on a lovely, leafy allotment with ample OSP, spacious shed, and level lawn, this beautiful home offers every element for enviable indoor-outdoor living.
The meticulously presented and move-in ready interior makes it easy to imagine living here. The lounge with gently vaulted ceilings and warm wood fire flows seamlessly to the dining area and quality kitchen. For those who love to cook, the stainless steel appliances and timber floors are practical, while the stylish shaker cabinets and leadlight accents add just the right amount of character. The rumpus room is an appreciated extra, and the generous covered deck with hillside views is ideal for entertaining in every season.
Add to this the updated main bathroom and beautiful bedrooms, including the ensuite main. With gas ducted heating and split system heating/cooling, every moment in this home will be rich with comfort. Set to impress, this property is an obvious choice for fabulous family living.
Located just a short stroll to the main st, cockatoo creek park, primary school, tennis and bowls club as well as public transport.
- Lovely, leafy allotment with ample OSP, spacious shed, and level lawn
- Modern, move-in ready interior with 2 generous living areas
- Contemporary kitchen with leadlight accents, SS appliances, and timber floors
- Gas ducted heating, warm wood fire, and split system heating/cooling
- Covered deck with hillside views
**Contact Agent for more information**
Please note: All property details shown are correct at time of publishing. Some properties may have been sold in the preceding 24 hours and we recommend that you confirm open for inspection times with the listing agent direct or the listing office.

Description:
YOUR OWN PIECE OF PARADISE!
***CLOSING DATE FOR OFFERS WEDNESDAY JUNE 10TH 6PM (UNLESS SOLD PRIOR)***
Situated on a quiet street with one of your neighbours a farm, this land offers filtered views and the opportunity to build your dream home (subject to council approval) on this 1009m2 (1/4 acre block). If peace and quiet is what youre after and you want to escape the rat-race, here is the property for you.
The township of Cockatoo is located within an hours drive of Melbourne CBD and offers a great community. The location of this block offers access also to nearby Emerald within a 5 minute drive.
This property must be sold, so make sure you put your offer forward and dont miss out on this opportunity!
Please contract Mick Dolphin on 0429 684522 or Janet Hawkins on 0409 117 432 to arrange your inspection today.
Vacant Land
https://www.consumer.vic.gov.au/duediligencechecklist
Please note: All property details listed were current at the time of publishing.
With the COVID 19 outbreak, the health and wellbeing of our clients and staff is our highest priority.
We are all taking extra measures to protect our clients and staff from coming into contact with the virus. Please help us by respecting our request that you do not attend an Inspection or the office if you have:
- Tested positive to Coronavirus
- Symptoms associated with Coronavirus
- Recently been in contact with someone diagnosed with Coronavirus
- Recently been overseas
- Agreed to any self-isolation conditions
We also ask that you practice social distancing from anyone attending the office or at an inspection, and where possible refrain from touching surfaces. We also appreciate your understanding as we are only able to have 10 people view the interior of the property at a time.
Thank you for your understanding
